att(pro29, pro7).  % [undermining] conf=80 — The WHO mortality data challenges pro7's premise that restricting abortion does not endanger women's health.
att(con23, pro29b).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — Con's pledge to end abortion directly contradicts the pro argument’s implied conclusion that legal abortion is needed to reduce maternal deaths.
att(con152, pro29b).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — Con’s introduction of anti‑abortion legislation opposes the pro claim that safe, legal abortion is necessary to prevent maternal deaths.
att(con23, pro7).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — Con23’s commitment to ending all abortion contradicts pro7’s allowance for abortion after viability with health exceptions.
att(con152, pro7).  % [rebuttal] conf=92 — The Life at Conception Act seeks a total ban from conception, which opposes pro7’s position that abortion may be permitted after viability.
att(pro63, pro7).  % [rebuttal] conf=70 — B states that not all abortions are unjustified, directly contradicting A's implication that abortions after viability are unjustified except for maternal health.
